WEBVTT

00:03.269 --> 00:05.204
Twilight: I have to admit
I was a little shocked

00:05.306 --> 00:06.639
when Princess
Celestia told me

00:06.740 --> 00:08.973
she wanted to start a
Scholastic Buckball league,

00:09.076 --> 00:10.876
but I was even more
surprised that she wanted

00:10.978 --> 00:13.779
the first game to be between
her school and ours!

00:13.981 --> 00:16.481
Apparently, she's
a huge sportsfan.

00:16.583 --> 00:18.684
I always thought Celestia
was kind of a jock.

00:18.786 --> 00:20.785
Just with really
wavy hair.

00:22.055 --> 00:23.722
Anyway, we don't
have much time.

00:23.824 --> 00:25.157
The game is in
two weeks!

00:25.459 --> 00:28.160
And I want all of YOU
to coach the team!

00:31.865 --> 00:33.032
I know how you feel.

00:33.234 --> 00:35.167
Young athletes ready
to take the field...

00:35.269 --> 00:38.036
Ooh! You can almost
breathe in the excitement!

00:40.007 --> 00:42.841
I don't think you should
breathe it in so hard!

00:46.380 --> 00:48.380
It's just... two
weeks doesn't feel

00:48.482 --> 00:51.750
like a whole lot of time
to train a <i>whole team</i>.

00:52.052 --> 00:53.518
Maybe the
School of Magic

00:53.620 --> 00:55.053
could play a few
other schools first.

00:55.155 --> 00:56.688
Like the Mane and
Tail Styling College,

00:56.790 --> 00:58.357
or the Scroll-Making
Institute?

00:58.559 --> 01:00.592
Relax. You're
gonna do just fine.

01:00.694 --> 01:03.562
Um... what makes
you so sure?

01:03.664 --> 01:05.897
Because I have faith
in my friends...

01:06.099 --> 01:07.732
who also
happen to be..

01:07.834 --> 01:10.469
the best buckball
players in Equestria!

01:10.771 --> 01:12.504
Oh, yeah!

01:12.606 --> 01:24.478
♪♪

01:24.585 --> 01:26.752
I guess that is
sort of true.

01:27.054 --> 01:28.820
I asked Rainbow
Dash to help too.

01:28.922 --> 01:29.755
But I'm not sure
where she...

01:31.024 --> 01:32.758
Sorry I'm late! But when
Twilight said she needed

01:32.860 --> 01:34.059
my help with the
buckball team,

01:34.161 --> 01:35.627
I figured I'd better
grab every piece of

01:35.729 --> 01:37.429
coaching equipment
I could find!

01:39.266 --> 01:40.832
So, what should
I focus on?

01:40.934 --> 01:43.235
Offense? Defense?
Trick plays?

01:43.637 --> 01:46.105
I was thinking of something
even more important!

01:46.207 --> 01:48.540
Awesome! Lay it on
me! Whatever it is,

01:48.842 --> 01:51.243
I'll give it a hundred
and twenty percent!

01:51.345 --> 01:53.545
I knew I could count
on your enthusiasm!

01:53.647 --> 01:57.049
That's why I want you to
coach.. the Cheer Squad!

02:00.487 --> 02:01.986
CHEERLEADING?

02:41.562 --> 02:46.598
♪♪

02:46.800 --> 02:48.967
I don't mean to
sound ungrateful...

02:49.069 --> 02:50.536
It's just, when you
said you wanted my help

02:50.638 --> 02:52.671
with something important,
I thought you meant...

02:52.973 --> 02:54.606
something important.

02:54.708 --> 02:56.842
The Cheer Squad
IS important.

02:57.444 --> 03:01.380
Bah-ha-ha! Oh.

03:01.482 --> 03:04.182
Well, sure Cheer Squad
is <i>totally</i> important

03:04.284 --> 03:05.951
to somepony
who isn't me,

03:06.053 --> 03:08.520
but I'm more about ponies
playing <i>in</i> the game,

03:08.622 --> 03:09.955
not cheering for it.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.126
I mean, it's great
that someponies

03:14.228 --> 03:16.995
only want to cheer, though I
don't know why they would.

03:17.097 --> 03:20.098
Hm. Well, maybe this will
be a good opportunity

03:20.200 --> 03:21.433
for you to find out.

03:21.735 --> 03:24.036
Of course I've seen
cheer squads before...

03:24.138 --> 03:25.071
On the sidelines...

03:25.172 --> 03:27.805
But I'm not even a hundred
percent sure what they do.

03:27.908 --> 03:29.241
I'll probably
just mess it up.

03:29.443 --> 03:31.210
I think you might
be surprised.

03:31.412 --> 03:33.512
In fact, I'm more
sure than ever

03:33.614 --> 03:35.413
that you're the
perfect choice!

03:36.684 --> 03:40.686
I'm actually 120
percent sure!

03:40.788 --> 03:42.588
And it's a good
thing too...

03:42.690 --> 03:45.524
The cheer squad
REALLY needs you.

03:45.726 --> 03:46.892
What do you mean?

03:46.994 --> 03:50.395
Well, I've been helping out
and let's put it this way.

03:50.497 --> 03:52.798
We've got two weeks
until the big game

03:52.900 --> 03:55.534
and.. we could
use two years...

03:55.736 --> 03:58.003
But that's all
gonna change

03:58.205 --> 04:01.907
because you're here
to save the day!

04:02.309 --> 04:05.911
Oh...kay. So why
are <i>you</i> here?

04:06.113 --> 04:08.413
What, a pony can't
show school spirit?

04:08.515 --> 04:10.349
You don't even go
to this school.

04:10.551 --> 04:13.986
Ah OK, when I went to the
Buckball Hall of Fame,

04:14.688 --> 04:18.257
I found out buckball
souvenirs are BIG bits!

04:18.359 --> 04:20.059
If Twilight's
team does well,

04:20.161 --> 04:22.862
I can start selling them
full time in Ponyville,

04:23.364 --> 04:25.898
so <i>I</i> have a
vested interest

04:26.000 --> 04:29.168
and <i>you</i> have an
assistant coach!

04:33.807 --> 04:34.873
She's here!

04:34.975 --> 04:36.208
Get the lights!

04:38.779 --> 04:41.580
<i> Over, and over,</i>
<i> and over again!</i>

04:41.682 --> 04:43.549
<i> We wanna dance</i>
<i> for each other</i>

04:43.651 --> 04:45.317
<i> and for all of</i>
<i> our friends!</i>

04:46.320 --> 04:47.820
Dancing. Right.

04:48.122 --> 04:50.422
I've seen you two around
school, haven't I?

04:50.524 --> 04:53.959
[giggle] I'm Shimmy Shake, and
this is Lighthoof!

04:54.061 --> 04:56.828
And we are your
lead dancers!

04:59.433 --> 05:01.833
I didn't know you
three would be here...

05:03.036 --> 05:05.504
Yona want to cheer
and make pony pyramid!

05:07.941 --> 05:09.508
And I thought this
could be my chance

05:09.610 --> 05:11.977
to make an impression
on everypony!

05:12.379 --> 05:14.947
You know, for something
other than changing shape...

05:15.649 --> 05:18.550
I didn't realize you were
into school spirit, Smolder.

05:18.752 --> 05:21.586
Uh, I just came with these
two. Guess they think

05:21.688 --> 05:23.889
you can make cheer
squad cool or something...

05:24.091 --> 05:25.490
Don't count on it.

05:26.627 --> 05:29.361
OK, now that we're all
here, why don't you

05:29.463 --> 05:31.730
tell us the plan? How
are you gonna make

05:31.832 --> 05:35.301
us into the most awesome
cheer squad ever!?

05:36.103 --> 05:37.870
Uh, I dunno.

05:40.241 --> 05:42.674
I mean, if you guys were
an actual buckball team,

05:42.779 --> 05:44.462
I'd have plenty of ideas,

05:45.363 --> 05:47.446
but I don't know anything
about cheerleading.

05:47.948 --> 05:50.949
Oh, ha-ha, yes.
Good one, coach!

05:51.051 --> 05:53.652
But Headmare Twilight
picked you for the job,

05:53.754 --> 05:57.823
so I'm pretty sure you
know what you're doing.

05:58.125 --> 05:59.391
If you say so...

05:59.893 --> 06:02.894
Ha-ha. Right.
OK, gang.

06:02.996 --> 06:05.731
Let's show Rainbow Dash
what we've been working on

06:05.833 --> 06:07.933
and she can take
it from there.

06:08.035 --> 06:09.100
Cheer Squad can do that!

06:10.871 --> 06:13.672
Yep! All we need
is a little music!

06:14.674 --> 06:16.742
<i> ♪♪</i>

06:16.844 --> 06:21.580
<i> Over, and ove-wah!</i>
<i> and ove-wah! again!</i>

06:23.083 --> 06:25.951
<i> We wanna dance....</i>
<i> for each other</i>

06:26.053 --> 06:27.986
<i> and for all of</i>
<i> our fri-ahhh</i>

06:28.088 --> 06:29.654
♪♪

06:29.756 --> 06:32.791
2, 4, 6, 8.

06:34.295 --> 06:37.396
[quietly] <i> ...Friendship School</i>
<i> is really great...</i>

06:37.498 --> 06:39.197
♪♪

06:44.004 --> 06:46.038
Well, that was
a disaster.

06:46.140 --> 06:47.973
It's kind of hard to
stick to our choreography

06:48.075 --> 06:49.541
when the floor
is moving.

06:49.943 --> 06:53.445
Yeah, Yona. Your stomps
are a little <i>too</i> powerful.

06:53.547 --> 06:55.681
Can we make pony
pyramid instead?

06:55.883 --> 06:57.249
Maybe we should
figure out

06:57.351 --> 06:59.051
which cheers we
should do first.

06:59.153 --> 07:02.221
Tss. Yeah. Because that'll
fix everything...

07:02.423 --> 07:06.591
So.. I mean there's a few,
uh, a lot of problems,

07:06.693 --> 07:09.094
but nothing you
can't solve. Right?

07:09.196 --> 07:10.729
Huh? Oh. Yeah.

07:10.831 --> 07:13.298
Listen, you guys don't have
anything to worry about.

07:13.500 --> 07:14.433
We don't?

07:14.635 --> 07:17.436
Nope. In fact, I think
what you all just did

07:17.538 --> 07:20.272
is totally fine. You
guys have got this!

07:20.374 --> 07:22.708
So... I'm just gonna
head down to the field.

07:23.310 --> 07:24.809
Great practice,
everypony!

07:31.218 --> 07:33.118
♪♪

07:33.220 --> 07:35.187
Oof! What are
you doing!?

07:35.689 --> 07:37.622
What are YOU doing?

07:37.724 --> 07:40.225
You gotta come back
and coach the Squad!

07:41.295 --> 07:44.162
I watched some cheer
stuff. Looked fine to me.

07:44.764 --> 07:47.599
Well, it's not! Do you
know what'll happen

07:47.701 --> 07:50.301
if they do what they
just did at the big game?

07:50.803 --> 07:52.237
Uh... nothing?

07:52.339 --> 07:54.139
Uh wrong!

07:54.441 --> 07:55.207
Oooh!

07:55.409 --> 07:58.643
A good cheer squad
gets the fans excited,

07:58.745 --> 08:00.612
which gets the
team excited.

08:00.814 --> 08:02.748
But if nopony's
excited,

08:02.850 --> 08:06.918
then nopony.. buys..
any.... SOUVENIERS!

08:07.020 --> 08:10.455
I THINK you're blowing this
a little out of proportion!

08:10.557 --> 08:13.592
Point is, if I'm
going to make any bits

08:13.694 --> 08:16.762
at these games, that
squad has to get better!

08:16.864 --> 08:19.964
And to do that,
they need a <i>coach</i>!

08:20.868 --> 08:24.503
You know what? You're
right! Why don't you do it?

08:24.605 --> 08:27.438
I mean <i>you're</i> the one
with a vested interest!

08:30.611 --> 08:32.911
The trick to being a
good buckball keeper

08:33.013 --> 08:34.746
is to do nothing.

08:34.848 --> 08:39.484
Just empty your
mind. Be the ball!

08:40.186 --> 08:42.821
Uh, balls don't
have minds.

08:43.123 --> 08:44.689
Exactly.

08:46.093 --> 08:51.496
♪♪

08:51.798 --> 08:52.798
Where's my
blindfol-

08:52.900 --> 08:56.432
<i> My turn!</i>
<i> I wanna do that!</i>
<i> Come on! Over here!</i>

08:56.537 --> 08:58.870
Why are you watching
Snail's weird practice

08:58.972 --> 09:01.240
when you're supposed to
be practicing with us?

09:01.342 --> 09:04.410
Heh heh. Snail's practice
is definitely weird.

09:04.912 --> 09:07.612
Uh, I thought Snips was
practicing with you.

09:07.814 --> 09:09.114
He <i>was</i>...

09:10.317 --> 09:12.451
Uh. Do you have any
idea how hard it is

09:12.553 --> 09:14.053
to dance in this stuff?

09:14.455 --> 09:16.555
Plus all these buttons
jingle so much,

09:16.657 --> 09:18.290
you can't hear
my cheers.

09:18.592 --> 09:20.259
Speaking up might
help a little.

09:20.561 --> 09:22.728
So don't dance
and cheer...

09:22.930 --> 09:25.797
Uh, then what
Cheer Squad do?

09:26.099 --> 09:26.765
I don't know.

09:26.867 --> 09:27.933
Maybe you should!

09:28.035 --> 09:30.335
...or whatever.
You're the coach!

09:30.437 --> 09:32.871
You're supposed to come up
with stuff for us to do.

09:33.073 --> 09:36.674
OK.... I've got something
for you to do.

09:37.178 --> 09:43.882
Just do nothing. Empty
your minds. Be the squad.

09:43.984 --> 09:46.017
We <i>are</i> the squad.

09:46.319 --> 09:47.352
Oh, yeah.

09:47.554 --> 09:50.755
At least helping sell my
souvenirs was.. something.

09:53.927 --> 09:57.530
Yona still not understand
how this make us better.

09:58.632 --> 10:02.568
Huh?! Professor Dash
needs to stay and coach!

10:03.070 --> 10:05.570
Ugh. You guys asked me
to come up with something

10:05.672 --> 10:06.838
and I did.

10:07.140 --> 10:08.907
I don't think
"nothing" counts.

10:09.209 --> 10:10.676
Then I'm out of ideas!

10:11.278 --> 10:13.778
This is the School
of Friendship.

10:13.880 --> 10:15.714
If you need ideas,

10:15.816 --> 10:18.450
you should ask your
friends for help.

10:19.352 --> 10:20.418
Fine.

10:20.820 --> 10:22.153
♪♪

10:22.255 --> 10:25.023
[no audible dialogue]

10:25.125 --> 10:42.197
♪♪

10:42.342 --> 10:45.944
OK, since you guys have
been nagging me non-stop

10:46.046 --> 10:48.914
about this cheer
stuff for, like, <i>ever</i>...

10:49.016 --> 10:50.816
It has literally
been one day.

10:51.018 --> 10:53.151
I went around and got
everything you need.

10:53.253 --> 10:57.956
♪♪

10:58.058 --> 11:00.259
Uh, what are we
supposed to do with hay?

11:00.461 --> 11:02.961
Beats me, but Applejack
seemed pretty sure about it.

11:03.163 --> 11:04.462
Oh! I almost forgot.

11:05.799 --> 11:07.599
A rhyming dictionary?

11:08.001 --> 11:10.502
Yeah. Zecora's a lot less
helpful then you'd think.

11:10.604 --> 11:13.004
That's from the library so
you can come up with cheers.

11:13.206 --> 11:14.806
OK! Good practice.

11:15.108 --> 11:17.009
So, you're just
leaving again?

11:17.711 --> 11:20.745
UGH! Look, I talked to
my friends and they said

11:20.847 --> 11:22.581
this is the
stuff you need.

11:22.683 --> 11:25.283
Wouldn't a <i>true</i> cheer
squad be able to figure out

11:25.385 --> 11:27.018
<i>what</i> to do with it?

11:27.320 --> 11:29.788
But Futtershy and Pinkie
want us to show them

11:29.890 --> 11:32.090
everything we've come
up with <i>tomorrow</i>!

11:32.292 --> 11:34.092
They want us to get
the team all excited

11:34.194 --> 11:35.727
before the big game!

11:36.329 --> 11:39.230
Well, then it's a good thing
I got you all this stuff.

11:39.332 --> 11:40.465
You'd better
get to work!

11:44.371 --> 11:45.403
Don't look at me!

11:46.773 --> 11:55.345
♪♪

11:55.415 --> 11:58.150
Good work, everypony.
Let's take a break.

12:00.721 --> 12:06.992
Yeah! [whistle] Wow. This team is
really shaping up! Nice job!

12:07.294 --> 12:10.395
Thanks. I'm excited to see
what you've been up to.

12:10.497 --> 12:13.298
Yeah! I can't wait to
see the Cheer Squad.

12:13.400 --> 12:18.503
HA, HA, HA! Oh,
you're serious.

12:19.305 --> 12:22.741
WOOOO-HOOOO! GO TEAM!
This is so exciting!

12:23.043 --> 12:26.144
Well, I'm sure you've put
in a lot of hard work.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.647
How much work does
cheer squad need?

12:28.849 --> 12:30.682
Anypony wanna buy
an official

12:30.784 --> 12:33.552
School of Friendship
Cheer Squad headband?

12:33.854 --> 12:38.156
Now I personally would buy
them <i>before</i> the performance.

12:38.758 --> 12:39.458
Huh?

12:39.560 --> 12:44.262
<i> ♪♪</i>

12:44.364 --> 12:47.665
<i> Over, and over,</i>
<i> and over again!</i>

12:49.970 --> 12:51.670
<i> We wanna dance</i>
<i> for each other</i>

12:51.772 --> 12:53.438
<i> and for all of</i>
<i> our friends!</i>

12:53.740 --> 12:57.108
School of Friendship
Rah-rah-rah.

12:57.410 --> 13:03.281
Let's win this game and hit
the-uh where is... spa?

13:09.456 --> 13:10.422
Yona!

13:10.524 --> 13:14.492
<i> ♪ [music intensifies] ♪</i>

13:17.464 --> 13:21.199
<i> ♪ [music droops and stops] ♪</i>

13:21.301 --> 13:24.035
I know I said I couldn't
wait to see the Cheer Squad,

13:24.137 --> 13:27.672
but maybe I could've waited
just a teensy bit longer.

13:27.774 --> 13:29.876
Rainbow: OH yeah!
Nice one!

13:31.578 --> 13:32.211
Huh?

13:32.813 --> 13:35.246
<i> ♪ [mournful music] ♪</i>

13:35.348 --> 13:36.147
What?

13:36.549 --> 13:38.982
♪♪

13:41.554 --> 13:44.222
I don't know what
everypony's so upset about.

13:44.524 --> 13:47.125
So it wasn't great.
Cheerleading's never great.

13:47.227 --> 13:49.794
That's why everypony gets
up to get a snack during it.

13:54.901 --> 13:56.768
What is the big deal?

13:56.970 --> 13:58.770
If you don't know,
there's no point

13:58.872 --> 14:00.872
in us trying to
explain it to you.

14:00.974 --> 14:02.873
Lead dancers out!

14:02.975 --> 14:03.742
Huh!

14:04.644 --> 14:06.577
It's not that
we were bad.

14:06.779 --> 14:08.346
It's that YOU didn't
even want to try

14:08.448 --> 14:09.915
to help us
get better.

14:10.717 --> 14:13.885
Didn't try? What are
you talking about!?

14:14.087 --> 14:16.087
I got you a party cannon!

14:16.189 --> 14:17.522
It's not my fault you
couldn't figure out

14:17.624 --> 14:18.990
how to use it right.

14:19.192 --> 14:21.559
Well, YOU could've
shown us!

14:22.829 --> 14:24.929
Whoa. Ponies might actually
care about cheer squad

14:25.031 --> 14:27.198
if she cheered like
that.. all the time.

14:27.400 --> 14:30.535
Why would you say ponies
don't care about Cheer Squad?

14:30.737 --> 14:32.437
Because they don't.

14:32.539 --> 14:35.540
No. YOU don't.
But THEY do.

14:35.842 --> 14:37.675
I bet Headmare
Twilight does!

14:37.777 --> 14:39.945
And you know what?
I do too!

14:40.247 --> 14:42.147
I actually got excited
when I found out

14:42.249 --> 14:43.982
you were gonna be
our coach. I figured,

14:44.084 --> 14:47.151
if anypony can make Cheer
Squad awesome, it's you.

14:47.453 --> 14:49.354
Me? Why?

14:49.756 --> 14:52.623
Because everything's
ALWAYS awesome with you.

14:52.725 --> 14:56.028
Or twenty percent
cooler... Or whatever!

14:57.030 --> 14:59.998
You're the most enthusiastic
pony in Equestria.

15:00.100 --> 15:02.501
When it's something
YOU care about.

15:02.903 --> 15:05.971
I just wish <i>we</i> were
one of those things...

15:09.042 --> 15:12.310
And it looks like my
assistant cheer coach

15:12.412 --> 15:15.680
slash souvenir-selling
business is a bust.

15:15.782 --> 15:17.482
So, I'm gonna take off,

15:17.584 --> 15:20.117
unless you can think of
something else for me to do?

15:22.088 --> 15:23.788
Maybe I can...

15:30.430 --> 15:31.496
Yak hate loud noises!

15:32.432 --> 15:34.765
Squad meeting.
Outside. ASAP!

15:35.167 --> 15:37.168
♪♪

15:39.906 --> 15:42.640
Dance ponies. Buckball
field. Pronto!

15:48.048 --> 15:52.416
Hey! Dragon! Get out
here and join your squad!

15:54.854 --> 15:57.722
So, what? Is there some
new button you wanna sell?

15:57.824 --> 15:59.457
Not a button....

16:00.660 --> 16:02.527
<i> ♪ [heroic music] ♪</i>

16:02.629 --> 16:04.028
Ugh not this again.

16:04.130 --> 16:05.864
Sorry, we're not buying.

16:05.966 --> 16:08.900
Wait! Look, I know I
haven't been a great coach

16:09.002 --> 16:10.768
because I don't care
about cheerleading.

16:10.870 --> 16:15.807
BUT all of YOU do,
and I care about you.

16:16.109 --> 16:19.544
So I guess maybe I
care about Cheer <i>Squad</i>,

